===Alternative forms===
* Note that the {{w|Traditional Chinese|traditional form}} contains {{l|mul|𦥑}} (7 strokes) while Japanese {{w|kyūjitai}}, Korean {{w|Hanja}}, Vietnamese {{w|History of writing in Vietnam|Nom}} and mainland China's standardized form ({{lw|zh|新字形#新旧字形对照表|新字形}}, {{w|Xin Zixing}}) contains {{l|mul|臼}} (6 strokes) instead. Both of these forms are encoded under the same [[code point]]. This character may appear to be either <span style="font-size:xx-large;" lang="zh-hant">搜 </span> or <span style="font-size:xx-large" lang="zh-hans">搜</span> depending on the fonts available.
* A {{w|CJK Compatibility Ideographs|CJK compatibility ideograph}} exist at <code>U+FA8E</code> for the alternative Korean form which contains {{l|mul|𦥑}} (7 strokes).

