===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|手|alt1=扌|叟|ls=psc|c1=s|t1=hand|c2=p}}.

{{zh-m|叟|tr=-}} is the original character,  also meaning “to search”, and depicting a hand holding a torch indoors.

===Etymology 1===
{{zh-forms|ss=⿱由又|alt=捜,蒐,𢯱,𠮍,𢅢}}
Compare perhaps {{cog|my|ရှာ|t=to look for}}, {{m|my|ရှု|t=to look at}}; the former is a stronger semantic match, the latter a stronger phonetic match ({{zh-ref|Luce 1981}}).

